org.midao.jdbc.core.handlers.output.lazy

Interface LazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    LazyOutputHandler<T,S>, LazyScrollOutputHandler<T,S>, LazyUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>, OutputHandler<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BeanLazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler, MapLazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler

    public interface LazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>
extends LazyScrollOutputHandler<T,S>, LazyUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>

    If underlying JDBC Driver doesn't support scrollable/updateable ResultSet - exception would be thrown. In order to check if JDBC Driver supports such functionality - please read relevant JDBC driver documentation and/or create POC (Proof of concept).

    Scroll/Update supports only one ResultSet due to the fact that some JDBC Drivers close previous ResultSet before returning next one. In cases where multiple ResultSets need to be handled - please use cached or standard(non-scrollable/updateable) lazy output.
